				My Dream Server - RP
			</span></a></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				This is my dream server, for roleplayers only. Its only 1pm and I am doing this from my mind after thinking about it over night. <br>  <br> If this server would ever exist, There would have to be a switch over thing, so players could bring their characters from other server onto it. Available to ALL servers for about one day. To keep the number from growing far too large there would be a minimal screening process so only the roleplayers can get in. <br>  <br> All people on the server would be perma /rp tagged. P vs P or not, I have not come to that conclusion yet.  <br>  <br> There would be a notice for anyone starting a new player on the server, stating what roleplay roughtly, is and what you SHOULDNT do.  <br>  <br> The GM's on the server would make sure the names did not go out of a roleplay sence, Ie.. no names like 'Pollycracker' or things like that. Also, roleplaying would be an enforced rule.  <br>  <br> Stated in the notice would tell you that failure to roleplay, or be in character. Which means referring to saying things about xp, your computer or connection is punishable by being disconnected, or more severlly on a more harsh offense banning, or character removal.  <br>  <br> /ooc command would still be valid, I think /auction should be disabled on it, since it really isnt roleplay to yell across a whole zone to sell an item. They could just as easily shout it, or just advertise by a hangout.  <br>  <br> I do believe, with all my being that there would be enough people on this shard to compare to the other shards.  <br>  <br> This would also make me, and im sure many many many more people happy. Revisions to this, or comments are needed Im sure, feel free to critisize this, it is only what 'I' would like to see.  <br>  <br> =-- <br>  <br> concerning the server to server swap. It would half to be over a weeks time. Ie, an hour or two each day on every server for about a week. This would get 80-95% of all the roleplayers. It would need to be advertised heavily on msg boards and notices aswell.  <br>  <br> But then, I dont see this happening in the future. <br>  <br> Say before the transfer, in some kind of order before the switch, all characters on one server will be prefixed with a letter of the alphabet, or symbol or something. For each server it would be different so there would be no mix up.  <br> After this weeks time, you could page a gm and tell him your name, what it was before. The gm will do a search through all the characters and see if the name is already taken, if not he will return it. <br>  <br> Those with the same name could be affixed with just a symbol like ` at the end, which would not hinder roleplay much at all. Or, they could have the same name, just spelled a little different. This is hard to say, but i dont think that there are that many people with exactly the same name. Unless they ripped it off from a book or movie. <br>  <br> Yours Truly, <br>  <br> Earwig Quickfoot, <br> 
						<p><span class="SignatureTitle">-----signature-----</span>
