				But then again, even if they did not do any kind of server transfer. I would probably still make a slow move into the server. It would be tough though, I would imagine for all the other people who are higher then level 6. :) <br> Leaving behind a well role played level 46 ranger or something to persue one good thing, roleplaying. Otherwise I would not have mentioned the server trade. Since you would be losing much more then the bad players, you would lose some friends, family, items, well. A lot. Anyway, I was just curious to know even if they did not do a server transfer, would anyone else even make a character on this kind of server? <br>  <br> btw, If I have ever made a mistake on my posts by saying 'shard' instead of 'server'. Forgive me, my computer is not the very best, so I often play ultima online on the few roleplaying servers, what was left of them anyway. Now I am just into working behind the scenes in eq, anticipating the moment I can get a much better running computer. <br>  <br> Yours Truly, <br>  <br> Earwig Quickfoot.
